    dc:creator "Rasmussen, Arne Redsted; Sanders, Kate Laura; Guinea, Michael L.; Amey, Andrew P." ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Sea snakes in Australian waters (Serpentes: subfamilies Hydrophiinae and Laticaudinae) - a review with an updated identification key" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947296>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947298>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119732>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947300>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947302>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947304>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947306>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947308>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947310> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947296>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Elongated mental shield several times longer than broad (left): H. zweifeli. Mental shield not much longer than broad (right)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947296/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947298>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Ventrals (except on the throat) divided into pairs of overlapping scales (top): H. stokesii. Ventrals on the posterior part of the body divided into pairs of not overlapping scales (bottom): Microcephalophis gracilis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947298/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119732>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Blunt spines on rear edge of some of the head shields: H. peronii." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5119732/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947300>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Head elongated with snout bill-like and flattened, very wide gape: H. platurus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947300/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947302>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Scales in the lowermost scale rows on flanks enlarged compared to dorsal scales: H. curtus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947302/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947304>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Two or three series of spots or dark-edged markings between dark bands, head very small and body compressed posteriorly: H. macdowelli (juvenile pictured)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947304/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947306>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Spots on the flanks and between the bands: H. elegans." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947306/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947308>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. One or two rows of regular black pentagonal markings on the side, primary colour dark brown or black: H. czeblukovi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947308/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947310>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Body with ocelli on the sides, ground colour white: H. ocellatus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

